"'''America's Most Beautiful Roadster'''" or (AMBR) is an award given out at the [[Grand National Roadster Show]] since 1950.<ref>{{cite book|first=Matt|last=Doeden|title=Custom Cars|publisher=LernerClassroom|year=2007|ISBN=0822590123|page=28|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LwKmAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA28}}</ref><ref name=Autoweek>{{cite web|url=http://autoweek.com/article/classic-cars/whos-going-win-grand-national-roadster-show|publisher=AutoWeek|date=January 29, 2016|title=Who’s going to win the 2016 Grand National Roadster Show?|first=Mark|last=Vaughn}}</ref> It was started by Slonaker as a 9-foot "megatrophy" that engraved the winner's name on it.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6i22H3ue8zoC&pg=PA95|title=Classic Hot Rods|first=Bo|last=Bertilsson|publisher=MotorBooks International|year=1999|pages=95-96}}</ref><ref name=Ultimate24>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OtKWmLLiuTgC&pg=PA24|page=24|title=Ultimate Hot Rod Dictionary: A-Bombs to Zoomies|first=Jeff|last=Breitenstein|publisher=MotorBooks International|year=2004}}</ref> At that time, it was the largest trophy in the world.<ref name=Ultimate24/>
