'''Avedis Kendir''' (born 1959, Istanbul, Turkey) is a well-known [[Armenia]]n jeweler.<ref name="Avedis Kendir">{{cite web|title=Avedis Kendir|url=http://www.turkishculture.org/whoiswho/applied-arts/avedis-kendir-2331.htm|publisher=Turkish Cultural Foundation|accessdate=30 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Masters of Istanbul |url=http://www.mastersofistanbul.com/en/usta/73/avedis-kendir |accessdate=30 December 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100924092600/http://www.mastersofistanbul.com/en/usta/73/avedis-kendir |archivedate=24 September 2010 |df= }}</ref>
==Life and career== Of [[Armenian people|Armenian]] descent, Avedis Kendir was born to a family of Armenian immigrants from [[Sivas]], [[Turkey]]. After discontinuing education at the age of 10, Kendir began learning to make jewelry as an apprentice under an Armenian jewelry master Mateos Usta.<ref name="Biriz Jewellery Official Website">{{cite web|title=Biriz Jewellry Official Website|url=http://www.birizjewellery.com|accessdate=30 December 2012}}</ref> In 1980, Kendir founded the "Biriz Jewelry" company and opened his first store in 1983. He has been designing and making jewelry for since then. His style of jewelry is Art Nouveau, [[Art Deco]], and Ottoman stylization.<ref name="Avedis Kendir" /> He sells much of his designs at the Kempinski Hotel in [[Ciragan Palace]].<ref name="Jeweler Profile: Avedis Kendir">{{cite web|title=Jeweler Profile: Avedis Kendir |url=http://www.theguideistanbul.com/news/detail/670/Jeweler-Profile-Avedis-Kendir |publisher=Istanbul: The Guide |accessdate=30 December 2012 |date=June 18, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130123055517/http://www.theguideistanbul.com/news/detail/670/Jeweler-Profile-Avedis-Kendir |archivedate=23 January 2013 |df= }}</ref> Avedis Kendir has notable clientele such as the [[Elizabeth II|Queen Elizabeth]] (who has bought numerous pieces), wife of [[Abdullah Gul]], and Elizabeth Taylor.
