'''Jan Hinnekens''' (died 2013) was President of the Belgian Catholic Farmers organisation (Dutch: Boerenbond) from 1981 to 1992. In 1992, he was succeeded by Robert Eeckloo. He was a member of the [[Coudenberg group]], a Belgian federalist [[think tank]] and of the [[Trilateral Commission]]. He is married with Marie Parein and together they have four children.
He died in October 2013. ==Sources== * Jan Hinnekens, ''Ontstaan en groei van het sociaal katholicisme in België'', Christelijke organisaties in nieuw perspectief, Antwerpen, 1966 * [http://www.namebase.org/sources/SD.html Trilateral Commission]{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} ([https://www.webcitation.org/64k856Ids Archive]) (members 6 April 1992)
