{{Infobox Politician |honorific-prefix = [[The Honourable]] | name = Roshi Bhadain | image = | caption = | order = [[Leader of Reform Party]] | birth_date = | birth_place = | spouse = | children = | party = [[Reform Party (Mauritius)|Reform Party]]<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Bastien|first1=Estelle|title=Roshi Bhadain lance son parti politique, The Reform Party|journal=lexpress.mu|date=27 January 2017|url=https://www.lexpress.mu/article/298884/roshi-bhadain-lance-son-parti-politique-reform-party|accessdate=5 February 2017|language=fr}}</ref> ''(present)'' | occupation = Politician | religion = Hindu | website = www.roshi-bhadain.com }}
'''Roshi Bhadain''' (born 25 April) is a [[Mauritian]] politician. He was also Minister of Financial Services, Good Governance and Institutional Reforms<ref>{{cite web|last1=(http://www.hydrant.co.uk)|first1=Site designed and built by Hydrant|title=Mauritius good governance law can inspire Commonwealth countries {{!}} The Commonwealth|url=http://thecommonwealth.org/media/news/mauritius-good-governance-law-can-inspire-commonwealth-countries|website=thecommonwealth.org|language=en}}</ref> under the government of [[Militant Socialist Movement]]. He is the leader of the Reform Party [[Mauritius]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Roshi Bhadain lance le Reform Party {{!}} Le Mauricien|url=http://www.lemauricien.com/article/roshi-bhadain-lance-reform-party|website=www.lemauricien.com|language=fr}}</ref> which has been founded in 2017..
==Education and Professional career== Roshi Bhadain is a Barrister-at-Law in Mauritius and a Fellow Chartered Certified Accountant with over 18 years investigative experience in fraud, financial crime, corruption and money laundering.
